# Frontend conventions
- Server Components by default; add `"use client"` only when the component needs state, effects, or browser APIs.
- Named exports only (except a route's default page/layout export).
- Keep components under ~200 lines; extract subcomponents when they grow.
- Tailwind for styling; use shadcn/ui primitives; no inline style objects unless truly necessary.
- Motion via framer-motion; every animation must honor `prefers-reduced-motion`.
- Accessibility: semantic elements, keyboard focus states, alt text, WCAG AA contrast.
- Data types are the source of truth: derive UI from the zod `Project` schema; never hardcode shapes.
- No `localStorage`/`sessionStorage` assumptions in SSR paths; guard browser-only code.
- Before using an unfamiliar API of a library in this repo, pull its docs via Context7 first.
